org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes

Class ASFileScope

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes.ASScopeBase
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes.ASScope
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes.ASFileScope
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IASScope, IFileScope
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FXGFileScope, MXMLFileScope, SWCFileScopeProvider.SWCFileScope

    public class ASFileScope
extends ASScope
implements IFileScope
    IASScope implementation for FileNodes. Conceptually, the file scope contains all top-level definitions in the file. Any top-level definitions that don't reside in packages are in the scope itself (see ASScope). This scope's implementations of findDefinitionByName, findAllDefinitionsByName, and findAllDefinitions also look for definitions in package scopes within the file. That way, we use the versions of these classes in the (possibly unsaved) file, rather than the versions that are stored in the project scope.
